ðŸ“± REACT NATIVE - CREATE ACCOUNT GROUP

**PURPOSE**: Create new account group with validation

**WHEN TO CALL**:
- When user submits creation form
- After validating all required fields

**PAYLOAD STRUCTURE**:
```typescript
interface CreateAccountGroupPayload {
  name: string;              // Required, max 255 chars
  code: string;              // Required, uppercase only, max 10 chars
  nature: 'assets' | 'liabilities' | 'equity' | 'income' | 'expenses';  // Required
  parent_id?: number | null; // Optional
  is_active?: boolean;       // Optional, default true
}
```

**CLIENT-SIDE VALIDATION**:
```typescript
const validateAccountGroup = (data: CreateAccountGroupPayload) => {
  const errors: Record<string, string> = {};

  // Name validation
  if (!data.name.trim()) {
    errors.name = 'Group name is required';
  } else if (data.name.length > 255) {
    errors.name = 'Name must not exceed 255 characters';
  }

  // Code validation
  if (!data.code.trim()) {
    errors.code = 'Group code is required';
  } else if (data.code.length > 10) {
    errors.code = 'Code must not exceed 10 characters';
  } else if (!/^[A-Z0-9_-]+$/.test(data.code)) {
    errors.code = 'Code can only contain uppercase letters, numbers, hyphens, and underscores';
  }

  // Nature validation
  if (!data.nature) {
    errors.nature = 'Account nature is required';
  } else if (!['assets', 'liabilities', 'equity', 'income', 'expenses'].includes(data.nature)) {
    errors.nature = 'Invalid account nature';
  }

  return errors;
};
```

**SUBMIT HANDLER**:
```typescript
const handleSubmit = async () => {
  try {
    // Validate
    const errors = validateAccountGroup(accountGroup);
    if (Object.keys(errors).length > 0) {
      setFormErrors(errors);
      Toast.show({
        type: 'error',
        text1: 'Validation Error',
        text2: 'Please fix the errors in the form'
      });
      return;
    }

    setSubmitting(true);

    // Submit
    const response = await api.post(
      `/accounting/account-groups`,
      {
        name: accountGroup.name,
        code: accountGroup.code.toUpperCase(),
        nature: accountGroup.nature,
        parent_id: accountGroup.parent_id,
        is_active: accountGroup.is_active
      }
    );

    // Success
    Toast.show({
      type: 'success',
      text1: 'âœ… Success',
      text2: response.data.message
    });

    // Navigate back or to details
    navigation.goBack();
    // Or navigate to details:
    // navigation.navigate('AccountGroupDetails', { 
    //   id: response.data.data.account_group.id 
    // });

  } catch (error) {
    if (error.response?.status === 422) {
      // Validation errors from server
      const serverErrors = error.response.data.errors;
      setFormErrors(serverErrors);

      // Show first error
      const firstError = Object.values(serverErrors)[0];
      Toast.show({
        type: 'error',
        text1: 'Validation Error',
        text2: Array.isArray(firstError) ? firstError[0] : firstError
      });
    } else {
      Toast.show({
        type: 'error',
        text1: 'Error',
        text2: error.message || 'Failed to create account group'
      });
    }
  } finally {
    setSubmitting(false);
  }
};
```

**SUCCESS RESPONSE (201)**:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Account group created successfully",
  "data": {
    "account_group": {
      "id": 15,
      "name": "Current Assets",
      "code": "CA-001",
      "nature": "assets",
      "nature_label": "Assets",
      "parent_id": null,
      "parent": null,
      "is_active": true,
      "is_system": false,
      "children_count": 0,
      "ledger_accounts_count": 0,
      "created_at": "2025-12-29T10:30:00.000000Z",
      "updated_at": "2025-12-29T10:30:00.000000Z"
    }
  }
}
```

**VALIDATION ERROR RESPONSE (422)**:
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Validation failed",
  "errors": {
    "code": [
      "This code is already used by another account group."
    ],
    "parent_id": [
      "Parent group must have the same nature"
    ]
  }
}
```

**BUSINESS RULES**:
1. **Code Uniqueness**: Code must be unique per tenant
2. **Code Format**: Uppercase letters, numbers, hyphens, underscores only
3. **Nature Matching**: If parent_id provided, parent must have same nature
4. **Tenant Isolation**: Parent must belong to same tenant
5. **Auto-uppercase**: Code automatically converted to uppercase

**ERROR HANDLING**:
```typescript
// Handle specific validation errors
if (error.response?.status === 422) {
  const errors = error.response.data.errors;

  if (errors.code) {
    // Duplicate code error
    Toast.show({
      type: 'error',
      text1: 'Duplicate Code',
      text2: 'This code is already in use. Please choose another.'
    });
  }

  if (errors.parent_id) {
    // Parent validation error
    Toast.show({
      type: 'error',
      text1: 'Invalid Parent',
      text2: 'Parent group must have the same nature'
    });
  }
}
```

ðŸ“± REACT NATIVE - LIST ACCOUNT GROUPS

**PURPOSE**: Display list of account groups with filtering and pagination

**WHEN TO CALL**:
- On Account Groups list screen mount
- When user applies filters
- When user searches
- When pagination changes
- On pull-to-refresh

**QUERY PARAMETERS**:
```typescript
interface ListParams {
  search?: string;           // Search in name or code
  status?: 'active' | 'inactive';  // Filter by status
  nature?: 'assets' | 'liabilities' | 'equity' | 'income' | 'expenses';
  level?: 'parent' | 'child';      // Filter hierarchy level
  sort?: 'name' | 'code' | 'nature' | 'created_at' | 'is_active';
  direction?: 'asc' | 'desc';
  per_page?: number;         // Default 15
  page?: number;             // Current page (handled by pagination)
}
```

**REACT NATIVE IMPLEMENTATION**:
```typescript
const AccountGroupsListScreen = () => {
  const [groups, setGroups] = useState<AccountGroup[]>([]);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
  const [refreshing, setRefreshing] = useState(false);
  const [pagination, setPagination] = useState<PaginationInfo | null>(null);
  const [statistics, setStatistics] = useState<Statistics | null>(null);
  const [filters, setFilters] = useState<ListParams>({
    search: '',
    status: undefined,
    nature: undefined,
    level: undefined,
    sort: 'name',
    direction: 'asc',
    per_page: 15
  });

  useEffect(() => {
    loadAccountGroups();
  }, [filters]);

  const loadAccountGroups = async (page = 1) => {
    try {
      setLoading(true);

      const params = new URLSearchParams();
      if (filters.search) params.append('search', filters.search);
      if (filters.status) params.append('status', filters.status);
      if (filters.nature) params.append('nature', filters.nature);
      if (filters.level) params.append('level', filters.level);
      if (filters.sort) params.append('sort', filters.sort);
      if (filters.direction) params.append('direction', filters.direction);
      params.append('per_page', filters.per_page.toString());
      params.append('page', page.toString());

      const response = await api.get(
        `/accounting/account-groups?${params.toString()}`
      );

      setGroups(response.data.data.account_groups);
      setPagination(response.data.data.pagination);
      setStatistics(response.data.data.statistics);
    } catch (error) {
      Toast.show({
        type: 'error',
        text1: 'Error',
        text2: error.message || 'Failed to load account groups'
      });
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
      setRefreshing(false);
    }
  };

  const handleRefresh = () => {
    setRefreshing(true);
    loadAccountGroups(1);
  };

  const handleSearch = useCallback(
    debounce((searchText: string) => {
      setFilters(prev => ({ ...prev, search: searchText }));
    }, 500),
    []
  );

  const renderItem = ({ item }: { item: AccountGroup }) => (
    <TouchableOpacity
      style={styles.groupCard}
      onPress={() => navigation.navigate('AccountGroupDetails', { id: item.id })}
    >
      <View style={styles.groupHeader}>
        <View style={styles.groupInfo}>
          <Text style={styles.groupName}>{item.name}</Text>
          <Text style={styles.groupCode}>{item.code}</Text>
        </View>
        <View style={styles.badges}>
          <View style={[
            styles.natureBadge,
            { backgroundColor: getNatureColor(item.nature) }
          ]}>
            <Text style={styles.natureBadgeText}>
              {getNatureIcon(item.nature)} {item.nature_label}
            </Text>
          </View>
          <View style={[
            styles.statusBadge,
            item.is_active ? styles.activeBadge : styles.inactiveBadge
          ]}>
            <Text style={styles.statusBadgeText}>
              {item.is_active ? 'Active' : 'Inactive'}
            </Text>
          </View>
        </View>
      </View>

      {item.parent && (
        <View style={styles.parentInfo}>
          <Icon name="trending-up" size={14} color="#6b7280" />
          <Text style={styles.parentText}>
            Child of: {item.parent.name} ({item.parent.code})
          </Text>
        </View>
      )}

      <View style={styles.counts}>
        <View style={styles.countItem}>
          <Icon name="folder" size={16} color="#6b7280" />
          <Text style={styles.countText}>
            {item.children_count} child groups
          </Text>
        </View>
        <View style={styles.countItem}>
          <Icon name="list" size={16} color="#6b7280" />
          <Text style={styles.countText}>
            {item.ledger_accounts_count} accounts
          </Text>
        </View>
      </View>

      <Text style={styles.dateText}>
        Created {formatDate(item.created_at)}
      </Text>
    </TouchableOpacity>
  );

  return (
    <View style={styles.container}>
      {/* Search Bar */}
      <View style={styles.searchContainer}>
        <Icon name="search" size={20} color="#9ca3af" />
        <TextInput
          style={styles.searchInput}
          placeholder="Search by name or code..."
          onChangeText={handleSearch}
        />
      </View>

      {/* Filters */}
      <ScrollView horizontal showsHorizontalScrollIndicator={false} style={styles.filters}>
        {/* Status Filter */}
        <TouchableOpacity
          style={[
            styles.filterChip,
            filters.status && styles.filterChipActive
          ]}
          onPress={() => showStatusPicker()}
        >
          <Text style={styles.filterChipText}>
            {filters.status ? `Status: ${filters.status}` : 'All Status'}
          </Text>
        </TouchableOpacity>

        {/* Nature Filter */}
        <TouchableOpacity
          style={[
            styles.filterChip,
            filters.nature && styles.filterChipActive
          ]}
          onPress={() => showNaturePicker()}
        >
          <Text style={styles.filterChipText}>
            {filters.nature ? getNatureIcon(filters.nature) : 'All Natures'}
          </Text>
        </TouchableOpacity>

        {/* Level Filter */}
        <TouchableOpacity
          style={[
            styles.filterChip,
            filters.level && styles.filterChipActive
          ]}
          onPress={() => toggleLevel()}
        >
          <Text style={styles.filterChipText}>
            {filters.level ? `${filters.level}s only` : 'All Levels'}
          </Text>
        </TouchableOpacity>
      </ScrollView>

      {/* Statistics */}
      {statistics && (
        <View style={styles.stats}>
          <View style={styles.statCard}>
            <Text style={styles.statValue}>{statistics.total_groups}</Text>
            <Text style={styles.statLabel}>Total</Text>
          </View>
          <View style={styles.statCard}>
            <Text style={styles.statValue}>{statistics.active_groups}</Text>
            <Text style={styles.statLabel}>Active</Text>
          </View>
          <View style={styles.statCard}>
            <Text style={styles.statValue}>{statistics.parent_groups}</Text>
            <Text style={styles.statLabel}>Parents</Text>
          </View>
          <View style={styles.statCard}>
            <Text style={styles.statValue}>{statistics.child_groups}</Text>
            <Text style={styles.statLabel}>Children</Text>
          </View>
        </View>
      )}

      {/* List */}
      <FlatList
        data={groups}
        renderItem={renderItem}
        keyExtractor={(item) => item.id.toString()}
        refreshControl={
          <RefreshControl refreshing={refreshing} onRefresh={handleRefresh} />
        }
        onEndReached={() => {
          if (pagination && pagination.current_page < pagination.last_page) {
            loadAccountGroups(pagination.current_page + 1);
          }
        }}
        onEndReachedThreshold={0.5}
        ListEmptyComponent={
          <View style={styles.emptyState}>
            <Icon name="folder-open" size={48} color="#d1d5db" />
            <Text style={styles.emptyText}>No account groups found</Text>
          </View>
        }
      />

      {/* FAB for Create */}
      <TouchableOpacity
        style={styles.fab}
        onPress={() => navigation.navigate('AccountGroupCreate')}
      >
        <Icon name="add" size={24} color="white" />
      </TouchableOpacity>
    </View>
  );
};

// Helper functions
const getNatureIcon = (nature: string): string => {
  const icons = {
    assets: 'ðŸ’°',
    liabilities: 'ðŸ“‹',
    equity: 'ðŸ¦',
    income: 'ðŸ“ˆ',
    expenses: 'ðŸ’¸'
  };
  return icons[nature] || '';
};

const getNatureColor = (nature: string): string => {
  const colors = {
    assets: '#10b981',
    liabilities: '#ef4444',
    equity: '#3b82f6',
    income: '#8b5cf6',
    expenses: '#f59e0b'
  };
  return colors[nature] || '#6b7280';
};
```

**RESPONSE FORMAT**:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Account groups retrieved successfully",
  "data": {
    "account_groups": [
      {
        "id": 1,
        "name": "Assets",
        "code": "AST",
        "nature": "assets",
        "nature_label": "Assets",
        "parent_id": null,
        "parent": null,
        "is_active": true,
        "is_system": false,
        "children_count": 3,
        "ledger_accounts_count": 5,
        "created_at": "2025-12-29T10:30:00.000000Z"
      }
    ],
    "pagination": {
      "current_page": 1,
      "per_page": 15,
      "total": 25,
      "last_page": 2,
      "from": 1,
      "to": 15
    },
    "statistics": {
      "total_groups": 25,
      "active_groups": 23,
      "parent_groups": 5,
      "child_groups": 20
    }
  }
}
```

ðŸ“± REACT NATIVE - ACCOUNT GROUP DETAILS SCREEN

**PURPOSE**: View complete details of an account group with relationships

**WHEN TO CALL**:
- When user taps on an account group from list
- After creating/updating to show result
- On details screen mount

**REACT NATIVE IMPLEMENTATION**:
```typescript
const AccountGroupDetailsScreen = ({ route }) => {
  const { id } = route.params;
  const [group, setGroup] = useState<AccountGroupDetails | null>(null);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);

  useEffect(() => {
    loadGroupDetails();
  }, [id]);

  const loadGroupDetails = async () => {
    try {
      setLoading(true);
      const response = await api.get(
        `/accounting/account-groups/${id}`
      );
      setGroup(response.data.data);
    } catch (error) {
      if (error.response?.status === 404) {
        Toast.show({
          type: 'error',
          text1: 'Not Found',
          text2: 'Account group not found'
        });
        navigation.goBack();
      } else {
        Toast.show({
          type: 'error',
          text1: 'Error',
          text2: error.message
        });
      }
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  };

  const handleEdit = () => {
    navigation.navigate('AccountGroupEdit', { id: group.account_group.id });
  };

  const handleDelete = () => {
    Alert.alert(
      'Delete Account Group',
      `Are you sure you want to delete "${group.account_group.name}"?`,
      [
        { text: 'Cancel', style: 'cancel' },
        {
          text: 'Delete',
          style: 'destructive',
          onPress: async () => {
            try {
              await api.delete(`/accounting/account-groups/${id}`);
              Toast.show({
                type: 'success',
                text1: 'âœ… Deleted',
                text2: 'Account group deleted successfully'
              });
              navigation.goBack();
            } catch (error) {
              Toast.show({
                type: 'error',
                text1: 'Cannot Delete',
